					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If I'm just playing samples and never manually feeding PCM samples through $4011, I should just leave the register totally alone, right? I just found a bug in ggsound where I had been writing this register every frame alongside sample playback. It only sounds correct vs. what I hear in FamiTracker when I totally leave $4011 alone. (interestingly, the only problem that it introduced when I HADN'T left it alone was very subtle differences in the pitch of the dpcm sample being played. Didn't notice it at all until now.)</div>

